28/*
29 * Some very early boards have problems loading firmware that is larger than
30 * 0x8000 words. In order to be able to provide at least *some* support
31 * for such ancient cards, an alternate firmware set is provided. This firmware
32 * isn't all that great, but, hey, it's better than nothing.
33 *
34 * Define USE_SMALLER_2100_FIRMWARE to select this.
35 */
36#ifndef USE_SMALLER_2100_FIRMWARE
37/************************************************************************
38 * *
39 * --- ISP2100 Fabric Initiator/Target Firmware --- *
40 * with expanded LUN addressing *
41 * and FcTape (FCP-2) support *
42 * *
43 ************************************************************************/
44/*
45 * Firmware Version 1.19.24 (14:02 Jul 16, 2002)
46 */
